<p><strong>Summary of Compiled Data: SCP-4011 Exploration 2052-12-26</strong></p>
<p><strong>Target Object:</strong> SCP-4011</p>
<p><strong>Relevant Foundation Assets:</strong> Mobile Task Force Upsilon-53</p>
<ul>
<li>U53-Mallow (PSHUD #411), MTF Lead</li>
<li>U53-Fenn (PSHUD #412), Specialist</li>
<li>U53-Lily (PSHUD #413), Technician</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> This is a summarized overview of the 2052-12-26 exploration into SCP-4011. For complete logs of video, network, and other sensory readings, contact the RAISA Central Office, extension 64011.</p>
<p><strong>Foreword:</strong> Previous exploration efforts had been hindered by SCP-4011-1, who withheld information and prevented free movement of MTF members, citing insufficient clearance. In order to gain a more complete understanding of the anomaly, Upsilon-53 Lead Mallow was granted temporary 5/4011 clearance, with the understanding that this clearance was provisional and only to be used to access the SCP-4011 facility.</p>
<div class="vcomms">
<p><strong>Reminder:</strong> Text marked in green indicates internal communications.</p>
</div>
<hr />
<p><strong>&lt;Begin Log Excerpt, 2052-12-26&#160;04:56 Earth-GMT&gt;</strong></p>
<p><em>[MTF Upsilon-53 enters SCP-4011. As in previous explorations, Upsilon-53 meets and authenticates credentials with an SCP-4011-1A instance, referred to as 1A-1.]</em></p>
<p><strong>1A-1:</strong> Verified. We apologize for the formalities, Overseer. Your task force has been cleared for entry. Do you require assistance in accessing the archives?</p>
<p><strong>U53-Mallow:</strong> That's alright, Archivist.<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-13" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-13')">13</a></sup> What is my clearance level as pertains to this site?</p>
<p><strong>1A-1:</strong> Overseer Mallow, your clearance codes are: 1/GENERAL, 5/4011 and therefore 5/Site-32M19, and 2/Area-R01. Would you like a full report?</p>
<p><strong>U53-Mallow:</strong> That won't be necessary. Are we permitted full access to this facility?</p>
<p><strong>1A-1:</strong> Yes.</p>
<p><strong>U53-Mallow:</strong> Then we'll be moving on.</p>
<div class="vcomms">
<p>&lt; U53-Lily&gt;: &quot;Overseer Mallow&quot;<br />
&lt; U53-Fenn&gt;: You're moving up in the world, Mal.<br />
&lt;%U53-Mallow&gt;: &quot;Minimum of communications,&quot; team. We're here to figure out where 4011-1 gets its information - let's stay focused on that.<br />
&lt;%U53-Mallow&gt;: Lily, keep track of -1Bs. If anything is causing these memory events,<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-14" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-14')">14</a></sup> it would be them.<br />
&lt; U53-Lily&gt;: Acknowledged.<br />
&lt; U53-Fenn&gt;: Hold on a moment.</p>
</div>
<p><strong>U53-Fenn:</strong> Archivist, what's the purpose of this site, again?</p>
<p><strong>1A-1:</strong> The mission statement of Site-32M19 is as follows: &quot;To maintain a comprehensive historical archive of the SCP Foundation and its subject peoples, and to maintain the security and sovereignty of the Foundation by&#8230;&quot;</p>
<p><strong>U53-Mallow:</strong> Archivist, you are permitted to speak the remainder of the statement.</p>
<p><strong>1A-1:</strong> &quot;&#8230;retroactively neutralizing evident threats through Protocol Alpha-1-7.&quot;</p>
<p><strong>U53-Mallow:</strong> What is Protocol Alpha-1-7?</p>
<p><strong>1A-1:</strong> Apologies, Overseer. We cannot further discuss Protocol Alpha-1-7 outside of the Alpha-1 Array<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-15" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-15')">15</a></sup>.</p>
<div class="vcomms">
<p>&lt;%U53-Mallow&gt;: That figures. We'll have to ask when we get down to B17.<br />
&lt; U53-Lily&gt;: They neutralize threats 'retroactively'?<br />
&lt; U53-Lily&gt;: And they have a seemingly-unlimited knowledge of history.</p>
</div>
<p><em>[MTF Upsilon-53 moves quickly through the upper floors of SCP-4011. The furthest previous expedition was forced to return before reaching Level B17 of the facility. The task force reaches this level at 05:15, after multiple clearance-verification checkpoints.]</em></p>
<p><strong>&lt;Timestamp: 2052-12-26&#160;05:15&gt;</strong></p>
<p><em>[MTF Upsilon-53 arrives at a large, reinforced door marked with a Foundation logo. A sign above reads &quot;Alpha-1 Array&quot; in English, as well as text in two other languages which are currently unknown and undergoing analysis. A -1A instance, denoted 1A-2, appears to be standing guard beside the door.]</em></p>
<p><strong>1A-2:</strong> Overseer.</p>
<p><strong>U53-Mallow:</strong> Archivist, we are entering the Alpha-1 Array. Open the door.</p>
<p><strong>1A-2:</strong> As you wish, Overseer.</p>
<p><em>[Two -1C instances embedded in the door lift it into the ceiling, revealing a long passageway lined with books of similar make to those listed in Appendix 3. -1C instances regularly move books between shelves and onward down the hallway, while -1B instances hover overhead. Most books in this area are marked with a vertical red stripe. MTF members continue down the passage.]</em></p>
<div class="vcomms">
