</div>
<p><strong>U53-Mallow:</strong> Lily, report!</p>
<p><strong>U53-Lily:</strong> It looks like 4011-1 compromised our comms. I would recommend deactivating network functionality and switching to voice-only.</p>
<p><strong>U53-Mallow:</strong> Approved.</p>
<p><strong>U53-Lily:</strong> Also, the entity had approximately three seconds of full access to our memories. I can't determine more without time and forensic analysis tools.</p>
<p><strong>U53-Mallow:</strong> Let's hope they didn't damage anything important. Onward.</p>
<p><em>[MTF Upsilon-53 moves further down the passage, scanning the titles of shelved books as they pass.]</em></p>
<p><strong>&lt;Timestamp: 2052-12-26&#160;05:22&gt;</strong></p>
<p><strong>U53-Fenn:</strong> Mallow?</p>
<p><strong>U53-Mallow:</strong> Hmm?</p>
<p><strong>U53-Fenn:</strong> Those books are titled &quot;History of the Foundation.&quot;</p>
<p><em>[U53-Fenn indicates a set of four books, each marked with a red vertical stripe.]</em></p>
<p><strong>U53-Mallow:</strong> Well that'd be an interesting find for Command.</p>
<p><em>[U53-Mallow approaches the shelf.]</em></p>
<p><strong>U53-Mallow:</strong> Archivist, we'll be transferring these books to another site.</p>
<p><em>[A hovering -1B instance responds (referred to as 1B-1)]</em></p>
<p><strong>1B-1:</strong> Confirmed, Overseer. A backup copy has been made. Note that those volumes were rendered outdated by Events A17-1 through A17-29.</p>
<p><em>[U53-Mallow removes the volumes. A summary of their contents is available in Addendum 3.]</em></p>
<p><strong>&lt;Timestamp: 2052-12-26&#160;05:25&gt;</strong></p>
<p><em>[U53-Lily has been reading Volume 4 of the recovered work.]</em></p>
<p><strong>U53-Lily:</strong> These pages say &quot;Pre-Revision Archive,&quot; and this book's &quot;Foundation&quot; <em>definitely</em> never existed. It looks like an ancient, theocratic version of our Foundation that was warring with the Daevites.</p>
<p><strong>U53-Mallow:</strong> Daevites? Do you think this is 140-related?</p>
<p><strong>U53-Lily:</strong> This one is set in the 15th century, so we're already past the black-zone for 140. It also shows the Daevites in control of far more territory than expected.</p>
<p><strong>U53-Fenn:</strong> Maybe this has something to do with &quot;retroactive neutralization?&quot;</p>
<p><strong>U53-Lily:</strong> Perhaps.</p>
<p><strong>&lt;Timestamp: 2052-12-26&#160;05:28&gt;</strong></p>
<p><em>[MTF Upsilon-53 reaches a large, cylindrical shaft, approximately 50 meters in diameter and with a glass-like floor and ceiling. Seven other corridors, identical to the one by which Upsilon-53 entered the chamber, extend outward. An unknown number of chambers can be seen stacked above and below, fading into a dull blue light. A metallic tower, 3 meters in diameter, stands in the center of the room, extending through all visible chambers. On each level, -1C instances move books between the eight spoke corridors and slots on the central tower, while -1B instances hover overhead. Five -1A instances stand around the tower, operating controls.]</em></p>
<p><em>[U53-Mallow approaches one of the central -1A instances.]</em></p>
<p><strong>U53-Mallow:</strong> Archivist&#8230; What is this?</p>
<p><strong>1A-3:</strong> This is the Alpha-1 Array. Directive Alpha-1 is currently active and- and holding blue.</p>
<p><strong>U53-Lily:</strong> Directive Alpha-1. Retroactive neutralization of threats to the Foundation.</p>
<p><strong>1A-3:</strong> That is correct, #413. The weeds, those who seek to smother the light of SCP, they are many. In a time long past, they grew very nearly too high, they nearly blocked out the sun of our Foundation. But now, with Protocol Alpha-1-7, we tear out the roots and the poisoned blooms fall and dissolve from memory. The Daeva-</p>
<p><em>[Approximately ten seconds of silence. Another -1A instance speaks.]</em></p>
<p><strong>1A-4:</strong> Alpha-1A identified. Initializing Protocol Alpha-1-7.</p>
<p><strong>1A-3:</strong> There was no time long past. The weeds are not and the weeds never were. SCP will always shine down upon us, the Foundation is-</p>
<p><em>[Approximately fifteen seconds of silence. A humming sound begins to emanate from the central pillar.]</em></p>
<p><strong>1A-4:</strong> Activating in five seconds.</p>
<p><strong>1A-3:</strong> Overseer Mallow.</p>
<p><strong>U53-Mallow:</strong> Archivist?</p>
<p><strong>1A-4:</strong> Activating.</p>
<p><strong>1A-3:</strong> What is SCP-140?</p>
<p><em>[A flash of light is seen from the tower. Audio and video recordings from MTF Upsilon-53 begin to show signs of severe corruption, rapidly becoming unsalvageable.]</em></p>
<p><strong>&lt;FEEDS CORRUPTED FOR 10 MINUTES 14 SECONDS&gt;</strong></p>
<p><strong>&lt;Timestamp: 2052-12-26&#160;05:41&gt;</strong></p>
<p><em>[MTF Upsilon-53 are sprinting through the upper floors of SCP-4011. U53-Mallow stops. She is carrying the four-volume &quot;History of the Foundation&quot; series recovered earlier.]</em></p>
<p><strong>U53-Mallow:</strong> What&#8230; just happened?</p>
<p><em>[U53-Fenn and U53-Lily stop]</em></p>
<p><strong>U53-Fenn:</strong> We were in 4011-2. There was a flash of light, and&#8230;</p>
<p><strong>U53-Lily:</strong> Our memories may have been compromised. We had been running toward the exit - recommend that we leave immediately.</p>
<p><strong>U53-Mallow:</strong> Approved.</p>
<p><em>[MTF Upsilon-53 exit the facility without further incident.]</em></p>
