<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">⯈&nbsp;Addendum&nbsp;6:&nbsp;SCP-4011-2</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">▼&nbsp;Addendum&nbsp;6:&nbsp;SCP-4011-2</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>SCP-4011-2 is a temporal modification device, currently believed to be the reason for which SCP-4011 was built. SCP-4011-1 regularly use this device, termed the &quot;Alpha-1 Array,&quot; to purge various people and groups from existence by retroactively disrupting the circumstances which led to their creation. The entities appear to perform this procedure, which they term &quot;Protocol Alpha-1-7,&quot; to neutralize persons and groups which present an existential threat to the SCP Foundation.</p>
<p>Because SCP-4011-2 acts retrocausally, it is currently not possible to detect or trace Alpha-1-7 Events. However, beings within SCP-4011 at the time of an Alpha-1-7 Event appear unaffected by it, and retain their memories of the previous timeline. SCP-4011-1 are, as such, unaffected by their own modifications to the timeline. They maintain an archive of civilizations and peoples, both in the current timeline and in those eliminated through Alpha-1-7 Events.</p>
<p>Through the monitoring efforts of MTF Upsilon-53, the effects of five Alpha-1-7 Events have been observed. A summary of the first encountered Alpha-1-7 Event is described below; all known information on the five observed events can be found in Supplementary Log 4011/5-2.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Summary of Alpha-1-7 Event</strong></p>
<p><strong>Reporting Individuals:</strong><sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-16" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-16')">16</a></sup> U53-Mallow, U53-Fenn, U53-Lily</p>
<p><strong>Target Persons or Groups:</strong> An anomalous group called the Nation of Lodia.</p>
<p><strong>State Before A17 Event:</strong> The Nation of Lodia began in 2046 as a covert society of anomalous humanoids. This society remained unknown to the Foundation until 2049, when it began to attack Foundation outposts using advanced anomalous technology. At least twelve sites were lost before the Alpha-1-7 Event in 2052.</p>
<p><strong>State After A17 Event:</strong> Foundation investigatory AICs discovered evidence of the Nation of Lodia only two months after its initial founding, and a raid on 2046-11-10 led to the dissolution of the group and the capture of key leaders. No further activity has been detected from the group.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>SCP-4011-1 has made frequent and vehement requests for access to SCP-140 since the events detailed in Addendum 5. In the course of these requests, it has revealed that it is unable to affect parts of the timeline overwritten by SCP-140 or destroy the object itself.</p>
<p>MTF Upsilon-53 has noted that, since beginning requests for SCP-140, SCP-4011-1A instances have spoken less coherently. Requests now include an increased number of pauses and verbal glitches, as well as an increasing use of religious imagery referring to a deity called &quot;SCP&quot; (see Addendum 3).</p>
<p>Following the events of Incident 4011-28, MTF Upsilon-53 are no longer able to access SCP-4011, and the Foundation is thus unable to detect further Alpha-1-7 Events.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
