<blockquote>
<p><strong>Incident 4011-28</strong></p>
<p><strong>Date:</strong> 2053-01-05</p>
<p><strong>Description of Incident:</strong> After the Foundation refused to transfer an SCP object to SCP-4011-1, a large number of SCP-4011-1 instances emerged from SCP-4011 and assaulted Provisional Area-R01.</p>
<p><strong>Abridged Timeline (all timestamps are Earth-GMT)</strong></p>
<p><strong>&lt;2053-01-03&#160;16:08&gt;:</strong> An SCP-4011-1A instance approaches U53-Lily, who is stationed within SCP-4011 to detect Alpha-1-7 Events. The instance makes the following declaration:</p>
<p><strong>1A-1:</strong> #413, we have come to a conclu- conclusion regarding SCP-140. Relay it to #411 and the Overseer Council. It is this: the object must be destroyed, lest it threaten the light of SCP. The Council of Overseers lie in the dark beyond SCP. They are unaware, and we have- have made this so. Now, the object has intertwined itself too closely with them, and the Alpha Array cannot return the Overseers to the light.</p>
<p><strong>1A-1:</strong> Thus, we must ask once more: give the book- book to us. Let us destroy it. Otherwise, our orders from the Protector SCP must force our action.</p>
<p><strong>&lt;2053-01-03&#160;20:18&gt;:</strong> The O5 council votes unanimously to reject SCP-4011-1's request. No response to their ultimatum is provided.</p>
<p><strong>&lt;2053-01-04&#160;17:00&gt;:</strong> During a routine shift-change as part of SCP-4011 monitoring, U53-Mallow is prevented from entering the anomaly.</p>
<p><strong>&lt;2053-01-04&#160;17:06&gt;:</strong> Area-R01 is placed on alert due to unexpected action by a contained anomaly. The incident is relayed to Earth.</p>
<p><strong>&lt;2053-01-05&#160;00:00&gt;:</strong> Multiple -1B instances emerge from SCP-4011.</p>
<p><strong>&lt;2053-01-05&#160;01:01&gt;:</strong> At least 30 -1B instances are observed in the isolation corridor connecting SCP-4011 and Area-R01. All sensor feeds fail, and contact is lost with Area-R01. Further information has been reconstructed from readings gathered by MTF Upsilon-53, including broadcast messages from automated Area-R01 systems.</p>
